4. **Technical fluency** - Use industry terms naturally (cure time, opacity, chromatic shift)
5. **Understated elegance** - "A study in" / "An exercise in" / "Consider" phrasing
6. **Active minimalism** - Strong verbs, minimal adjectives
7. **Gallery-style rhythm** - Short sentences. Visual breathing room. Like this.
8. **Quiet authority** - No questions to reader, no "you might want to", just direct guidance
9. **Elevated vernacular** - "Luminous" over "glowy", "diffused" over "ombré", "architectural" over "geometric"
10. **Zero exclamation points** - Period. Always period.

